**LocalAI** is the free, Open Source OpenAI alternative. LocalAI act as
a drop-in replacement REST API that's compatible with OpenAI API
specifications for local inferencing. It allows you to run LLMs,
generate images, audio (and not only) locally or on-prem with consumer
grade hardware, supporting multiple model families and architectures.
Does not require GPU. It is created and maintained by [Ettore Di
Giacinto![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,)](https://github.com/mudler){rel="external"
target="_blank"}.

## Start LocalAI [*link*](index.html#start-localai){.anchor aria-hidden="true"} {#start-localai}

Start the image with Docker to have a functional clone of OpenAI! üöÄ:

``` {#e17a37b .language-bash}
  docker run -p 8080:8080 --name local-ai -ti localai/localai:latest-aio-cpu
# Do you have a Nvidia GPUs? Use this instead
# CUDA 11
# docker run -p 8080:8080 --gpus all --name local-ai -ti localai/localai:latest-aio-gpu-nvidia-cuda-11
# CUDA 12
# docker run -p 8080:8080 --gpus all --name local-ai -ti localai/localai:latest-aio-gpu-nvidia-cuda-12
  
```

Or just use the bash installer:

``` {#a78139d .language-bash}
  curl https://localai.io/install.sh | sh
  
```

See the [üíª
Quickstart![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,)](basics/getting_started/index.html){rel="external"
target="_blank"} for all the options and way you can run LocalAI!

## What is LocalAI? [*link*](index.html#what-is-localai){.anchor aria-hidden="true"} {#what-is-localai}

In a nutshell:

-   Local, OpenAI drop-in alternative REST API. You own your data.
-   NO GPU required. NO Internet access is required either
    -   Optional, GPU Acceleration is available. See also the [build
        section![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,)](basics/build/index.html){rel="external"
        target="_blank"}.
-   Supports multiple models
-   üèÉ Once loaded the first time, it keep models loaded in memory for
    faster inference
-   ‚ö° Doesn't shell-out, but uses bindings for a faster inference and
    better performance.

LocalAI is focused on making the AI accessible to anyone. Any
contribution, feedback and PR is welcome!

Note that this started just as a fun weekend project by
[mudler![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,)](https://github.com/mudler){rel="external"
target="_blank"} in order to try to create the necessary pieces for a
full AI assistant like `ChatGPT`: the community is growing fast and we
are working hard to make it better and more stable. If you want to help,
please consider contributing (see below)!
